## PHASE 1: Get Real Weather Data

```
I need to fetch historical weather data for solar prediction using the 
Open-Meteo API (free, no API key needed).

Write a Python script (backend/data/fetch_data.py) that:
1. Fetches daily historical weather data for the last 2 years for a given 
   city (start with New Delhi, lat 28.6139, lon 77.2090)
2. Pulls these fields: temperature_2m_max, temperature_2m_min, 
   shortwave_radiation_sum (this is our solar irradiance proxy), 
   cloudcover_mean, relative_humidity_2m_mean, windspeed_10m_max
3. Saves the result as a clean CSV file in backend/data/weather_data.csv
4. Print the first 5 rows and basic stats (.describe()) so I can verify it worked

Use the Open-Meteo Archive API endpoint: 
https://archive-api.open-meteo.com/v1/archive

Explain each part of the code in comments as if I only know JavaScript, not Python.
```

