## How to use this well
- Do phases **in order** — each depends on the previous one working.
- After each phase, **run the code** and make sure it actually works before moving on.
- Ask VS Code AI "explain this part to me" on anything you don't understand — don't skip that step, it's what saves you in the viva.
- If something breaks, paste the exact error message back into the chat rather than re-describing the problem — AI debugs errors much faster than descriptions.